direction of the projection

00:02:03.080 --> 00:02:06.830
of the acceleration, a perp.

00:02:06.830 --> 00:02:09.139
The magnitude is
proportional to a perp,

00:02:09.139 --> 00:02:14.630
but only evaluated at retarded
time, t prime equal to t

00:02:14.630 --> 00:02:18.350
minus r/c, where r is
actually the distance

00:02:18.350 --> 00:02:22.640
between the observer and
the radiating charge.

00:02:22.640 --> 00:02:29.300
And the reason why we have this
t prime, the retarded time,

00:02:29.300 --> 00:02:32.960
is because of the speed of
propagation of information.

00:02:32.960 --> 00:02:35.810
So that's actually what
we discussed last time.

00:02:35.810 --> 00:02:40.980
