00:04:44.600 --> 00:04:50.130
And now we are in the position
to understand what is going on.

00:04:50.130 --> 00:04:54.290
So this is actually why
we can use polarizer

00:04:54.290 --> 00:04:58.720
to make such a good photo.

00:04:58.720 --> 00:05:03.290
So now we know what is actually
happening at the sun, right?

00:05:03.290 --> 00:05:04.910
So at the sun,
there are something

00:05:04.910 --> 00:05:06.680
which is oscillating--

00:05:06.680 --> 00:05:14.360
OK, some kind of
emission from the sun.

00:05:14.360 --> 00:05:17.720
And those emissions are not
correlated to each other.

00:05:17.720 --> 00:05:21.980
And that produces
unpolarized sunlight.

00:05:21.980 --> 00:05:24.760
So if you're looking
to the sun, you

00:05:24.760 --> 00:05:28.300
are looking at
unpolarized light.

00:05:28.300 --> 00:05:34.650
On the other hand, if you
are looking at the sky,

00:05:34.650 --> 00:05:40.020
roughly like 45 or 90 degree--

00:05:40.020 --> 00:05:44.110
OK, 45 degree from on the
sun, what is going to happen

00:05:44.110 --> 00:05:47.440
is that what you
are actually seeing,

00:05:47.440 --> 00:05:50.410
all this light from
the sky, actually,

00:05:50.410 --> 00:05:54.850
the sunlight after
scattering between sunlight

00:05:54.850 --> 00:05:58.930
and the dust in the air.

00:05:58.930 --> 00:06:03.930
So basically, on this
guide, in our air,

00:06:03.930 --> 00:06:06.310
there are many, many
little dust, right?

00:06:06.310 --> 00:06:11.360
And when light-- as
you shine on this dust,

00:06:11.360 --> 00:06:15.700
they change direction,
this so-called scattering.

00:06:15.700 --> 00:06:21.400
And those light are
collected by your camera.

00:06:21.400 --> 00:06:25.500
The interesting thing is that
if you have a molecule which

00:06:25.500 --> 00:06:30.040
is actually here, and you
have some unpolarized sunlight

00:06:30.040 --> 00:06:33.760
shining on this molecule,
and it changed direction

00:06:33.760 --> 00:06:40.640
by 90 degrees, what is going to
happen is that all the things--

00:06:40.640 --> 00:06:46.240
originally you have an
unpolarized sunlight.

00:06:46.240 --> 00:06:50.080
Therefore, you have all kinds
of different polarizations,

00:06:50.080 --> 00:06:53.210
if you look at the
electromagnetic wave.

00:06:53.210 --> 00:06:57.130
However, if you only choose
the light which are scattered

00:06:57.130 --> 00:07:00.870
and are going toward this
direction, apparently,

00:07:00.870 --> 00:07:04.240
the electromagnetic wave,
or the polarization,

00:07:04.240 --> 00:07:06.730
or let's say the direction
of the electric field,

00:07:06.730 --> 00:07:10.960
has to be perpendicular to
the direction of propagation.

00:07:10.960 --> 00:07:13.540
Therefore, what
is going to happen

00:07:13.540 --> 00:07:19.450
is that only this direction,
only the polarization

00:07:19.450 --> 00:07:22.085
in this direction, which is
perpendicular to the direction

00:07:22.085 --> 00:07:24.820
of propagation will survive.

00:07:24.820 --> 00:07:27.700
All the other
components, like the one

00:07:27.700 --> 00:07:31.810
which is pointing upward or
pointing downwards, or coming

00:07:31.810 --> 00:07:34.510
from the original
sunlight will not survive.

00:07:34.510 --> 00:07:38.920
Therefore, what is going
to happen is that when

00:07:38.920 --> 00:07:41.470
you do get 45 degrees--

00:07:41.470 --> 00:07:45.190
the sky 45 degrees from
the sun, the sunlight

00:07:45.190 --> 00:07:47.950
is actually what
kind of sunlight?

00:07:47.950 --> 00:07:51.160
Is polarized sunlight.

00:07:51.160 --> 00:07:54.730
Therefore, if you
tune your filter

00:07:54.730 --> 00:07:56.770
to be aligned with
the polarization,

00:07:56.770 --> 00:07:59.950
you will be able to
filter a large amount

00:07:59.950 --> 00:08:02.710
of the scattered sunlight.

00:08:02.710 --> 00:08:05.600
And that is actually
how this works.

00:08:05.600 --> 00:08:09.820
And then you can see that,
indeed, the sky becomes darker

00:08:09.820 --> 00:08:14.260
after you apply this polarizer
in front of your camera.

00:08:14.260 --> 00:08:17.950
So that's essentially the
first thing which we learn.

00:08:17.950 --> 00:08:20.440
The second thing is
that, OK, we also

00:08:20.440 --> 00:08:23.620
found that the polarizer
is particularly

00:08:23.620 --> 00:08:30.820
usefull for the filtering of the
reflected light on the window.

00:08:30.820 --> 00:08:35.080
And of course, we can also
use exactly the same technique

00:08:35.080 --> 00:08:37.150
to filter out the
reflected light

00:08:37.150 --> 00:08:40.240
from the water for dipole.

00:08:40.240 --> 00:08:41.770
And how does this work?

00:08:41.770 --> 00:08:45.670
And it turns out that this
actually much more complicated

00:08:45.670 --> 00:08:47.140
than what we thought.

00:08:47.140 --> 00:08:50.040
And we have to
actually derive this.

00:08:50.040 --> 00:08:54.220
And that is actually related
to the electromagnetic wave

00:08:54.220 --> 00:08:57.730
propagation inside
the material, and also

00:08:57.730 --> 00:08:59.740
related to Brewster's angle.

00:08:59.740 --> 00:09:01.790
And that is actually
the main topic

00:09:01.790 --> 00:09:04.570
which we are going
to talk about today.

00:09:04.570 --> 00:09:07.340
So let's immediately
get started.

00:09:07.340 --> 00:09:10.090
So now what we
are interested is,

00:09:10.090 --> 00:09:13.800
how does this actually work?

00:09:13.800 --> 00:09:15.700
And why is this happening?

00:09:15.700 --> 00:09:21.520
And why is the reflected
light become polarized?

00:09:21.520 --> 00:09:25.430
So that's the question
we are trying to answer.

00:09:25.430 --> 00:09:27.640
So we have talked about
electromagnetic waves

00:09:27.640 --> 00:09:28.940
in vacuum.

00:09:28.940 --> 00:09:32.320
And we also know how to
generate electromagnetic,

00:09:32.320 --> 00:09:35.690
and now we are interested
in electromagnetic wave

00:09:35.690 --> 00:09:37.600
in dielectrics.

00:09:37.600 --> 00:09:40.910
So we have talked about two
kinds of materials already.

00:09:40.910 --> 00:09:43.870
The first one is a
perfect conductor.

00:09:43.870 --> 00:09:46.120
And the second one which
we are going to talk about

00:09:46.120 --> 00:09:48.820
is a dielectrics material.

00:09:48.820 --> 00:09:53.680
In case of perfect
conductor, it costs nothing

00:09:53.680 --> 00:09:58.090
to move all the charges
inside this conductor around.

00:09:58.090 --> 00:10:02.860
And basically, that will give
you a zero electric field

00:10:02.860 --> 00:10:05.900
inside the conductor.

00:10:05.900 --> 00:10:09.760
And also, we have a
limited supply of charges.

00:10:09.760 --> 00:10:13.570
And therefore, inside this
kind of perfect conductor,

00:10:13.570 --> 00:10:16.630
there will be no electric field.

00:10:16.630 --> 00:10:21.130
On the other hand, if you have
a dielectrics material, what

00:10:21.130 --> 00:10:24.000
is going to happen
is that there are

00:10:24.000 --> 00:10:28.380
a lot of charges
inside the material,

00:10:28.380 --> 00:10:31.110
but all those
charges are attached

00:10:31.110 --> 00:10:34.050
to a specific atom or molecule.

00:10:34.050 --> 00:10:38.250
They cannot be moving
freely all over the place.

00:10:38.250 --> 00:10:41.550
And that is actually
so-called bound

00:10:41.550 --> 00:10:46.050
to the atom or the
location of the molecule.

00:10:46.050 --> 00:10:51.570
And that introduces a
little bit of complication.

00:10:51.570 --> 00:10:54.340
So this kind of
material, they also

00:10:54.340 --> 00:11:00.030
respond to the external magnetic
field or electric field.

00:11:00.030 --> 00:11:04.520
For example, in this case,
I have electron cloud which

00:11:04.520 --> 00:11:10.320
is around the nuclei in this--

00:11:10.320 --> 00:11:15.890
around the positive charge
nucleus in this figure.

00:11:15.890 --> 00:11:18.005
And you can see
that before we apply

00:11:18.005 --> 00:11:24.900
an external electric field,
it's symmetric around zero.

00:11:24.900 --> 00:11:30.720
After we introduce this electric
field, external electric field,

00:11:30.720 --> 00:11:34.830
there can be some kind
of polarization produced,

00:11:34.830 --> 00:11:40.140
because the electrons
around this nucleus

00:11:40.140 --> 00:11:46.710
can be moved slightly, such
that this material is actually

00:11:46.710 --> 00:11:50.100
trying to compensate a
little bit the effect

00:11:50.100 --> 00:11:52.500
of the external force.

00:11:52.500 --> 00:11:56.400
So that is actually
leading to a modification

00:11:56.400 --> 00:11:58.810
of the electric field.

00:11:58.810 --> 00:12:01.260
But as I mentioned,
you are not going

00:12:01.260 --> 00:12:06.420
to cancel all the effect
of the external field.

00:12:06.420 --> 00:12:09.340
So how do we understand this?

00:12:09.340 --> 00:12:11.700
The idea is the following.

00:12:11.700 --> 00:12:15.220
So since this system
is complicated,

00:12:15.220 --> 00:12:17.610
you have a free charge.

00:12:17.610 --> 00:12:22.380
It could have free charge
as we really kick out

00:12:22.380 --> 00:12:25.350
or add some electrons
into this system.

00:12:25.350 --> 00:12:28.350
It can have bounce charge.

00:12:28.350 --> 00:12:31.551
And if becomes a rather
complicated description.

00:12:31.551 --> 00:12:32.800
So the idea is the followiong.

00:12:32.800 --> 00:12:36.720
So in order to actually--

00:12:36.720 --> 00:12:40.710
for our convenience,
to be similar to what

00:12:40.710 --> 00:12:44.650
we have been doing
in vacuum case,

00:12:44.650 --> 00:12:48.510
our goal is to
define a field which

00:12:48.510 --> 00:12:53.520
is actually with the
material itself subtracted.

00:12:53.520 --> 00:12:59.310
In this case, what we can
do is to define a D field,

00:12:59.310 --> 00:13:03.300
which is related--

00:13:03.300 --> 00:13:05.400
we hope that this is
actually only related

00:13:05.400 --> 00:13:09.750
to the free charge
inside the material.

00:13:09.750 --> 00:13:11.910
And then we can actually
do all the tricks

00:13:11.910 --> 00:13:14.460
which is actually similar
to what we have already

00:13:14.460 --> 00:13:17.140
learned from the vacuum--

00:13:17.140 --> 00:13:21.090
Maxwell's equation to solve
the problems inside material.

00:13:21.090 --> 00:13:24.270
So that's essentially our goal.

00:13:24.270 --> 00:13:29.980
In order to do that, we have
to classify the total charge

00:13:29.980 --> 00:13:32.920
density, rho, into
two components.

00:13:32.920 --> 00:13:35.320
The first component
is the free charge,

00:13:35.320 --> 00:13:39.000
which essentially is the
charges which can travel freely

00:13:39.000 --> 00:13:41.250
inside the media.

00:13:41.250 --> 00:13:45.990
And the bound charge, which
is actually, as I mentioned,

00:13:45.990 --> 00:13:48.260
for example, those electrons--

00:13:48.260 --> 00:13:49.440
the electron cloud.

00:13:49.440 --> 00:13:55.310
And essentially, they are
bound around central location

00:13:55.310 --> 00:13:57.240
in the media.

00:13:57.240 --> 00:13:58.780
So the idea is the following.

00:13:58.780 --> 00:14:03.120
So I can now define a D field.

00:14:03.120 --> 00:14:10.170
This D field is a so-called
electric displacement field.

00:14:10.170 --> 00:14:17.682
It's defined as epsilon0 times
E field plus a P vector, which

00:14:17.682 --> 00:14:20.610
is the polarization vector.

00:14:20.610 --> 00:14:24.660
Where this P vector is
defined in the following way--

00:14:24.660 --> 00:14:31.050
minus divergence of the
P factor is actually

00:14:31.050 --> 00:14:37.020
equal to the bound charge
density, which is rho.

00:14:37.020 --> 00:14:41.550
If we have this definition
and we actually continue

00:14:41.550 --> 00:14:44.190
and write down the Gauss' law--

00:14:44.190 --> 00:14:48.600
and we can see that this is
the Gauss' law, epsilon0--

00:14:48.600 --> 00:14:54.180
divergence of E will
be equal to rho.

00:14:54.180 --> 00:14:57.680
And we also-- under
our classification,

00:14:57.680 --> 00:15:01.930
essentially, there are two
components, rho f and rho p.

00:15:01.930 --> 00:15:05.130
The bound charge
and the free charge.

00:15:05.130 --> 00:15:07.050
And according to
our definition, this

00:15:07.050 --> 00:15:13.980
can be written as rho
f minus delta P vector.

00:15:13.980 --> 00:15:16.200
And now what we
can do is that we

00:15:16.200 --> 00:15:21.270
can use the definition of the
electric displacement field

00:15:21.270 --> 00:15:24.620
and collect all the
terms except the rho

00:15:24.620 --> 00:15:26.460
f to the left-hand side.

00:15:26.460 --> 00:15:30.030
Then you will conclude
that the divergence of D

00:15:30.030 --> 00:15:33.470
will be equal to rho f.

00:15:33.470 --> 00:15:35.960
So after this
calculation, you can

00:15:35.960 --> 00:15:37.790
see that what we
have achieved is

00:15:37.790 --> 00:15:42.990
that we have defined a
field, a displacement field

00:15:42.990 --> 00:15:51.230
D, which is totally related to
the effect of the free charge.

00:15:51.230 --> 00:15:54.700
In this case, what we
derived is actually

00:15:54.700 --> 00:15:57.860
delta D equal to rho f.

00:15:57.860 --> 00:16:02.160
And this actually looks pretty
similar to the situation

00:16:02.160 --> 00:16:03.790
in vacuum, right?

00:16:03.790 --> 00:16:09.290
Because what we actually have is
epsilon0 delta E equal to rho.

00:16:09.290 --> 00:16:12.920
And after we actually remove
the contribution of the bound

00:16:12.920 --> 00:16:17.050
charge, this becomes
this expression.

00:16:17.050 --> 00:16:19.710
Any questions so far?

00:16:19.710 --> 00:16:22.910
All right, so this is
actually a purely definition.

00:16:22.910 --> 00:16:29.180
And we can also do a very
similar thing to the current.

00:16:29.180 --> 00:16:33.350
So the total current, J,
will have the following three

00:16:33.350 --> 00:16:34.680
components.

00:16:34.680 --> 00:16:36.830
The first component
is the free current,

00:16:36.830 --> 00:16:43.130
which is the current related
to free charge moving around

00:16:43.130 --> 00:16:46.190
inside this dielectrics method.

00:16:46.190 --> 00:16:48.950
There can be contribution
from the bound current.

00:16:48.950 --> 00:16:50.955
The bound current is
actually the current

00:16:50.955 --> 00:16:55.190
which is only moving around
some specific location.

00:16:55.190 --> 00:16:58.990
And finally, the
polarization contribution.

